# SPDX-License-Identifier: AGPL-3.0-or-later
# Trustfile — Trust boundaries and integrity invariants for 688 Attack Hub
# Author: Jonathan D.A. Jewell (hyperpolymath)
#
# What LLM/SLM agents are trusted to do without asking, and integrity
# invariants that verify the repo has not been tampered with.

@abstract:
Trust boundaries and integrity checks for 688 Attack Hub. This is a small,
single-file browser game with no server component and no dependencies — the
attack surface (see SECURITY.md) is deliberately small, and so is the trust
model.
@end

## Trust Level

Current trust level: standard

- Agent may read and edit the game file, docs, and machine-readable metadata
  freely.
- Adding a network call, `eval`, or `new Function` to the game requires
  explicit human approval first (see 0-AI-MANIFEST.a2ml invariants) — this
  is the one thing that would falsify AUDIT.adoc's central claim.
- Licence, org, and CLADE identity fields are maintainer-only.

## Integrity Invariants

### no-secrets-committed
- description: No credential files in repo
- run: test ! -f .env && test ! -f credentials.json
- severity: critical

### no-private-keys
- description: No private key files committed
- run: "! find . -name '*.pem' -o -name '*.key' -o -name 'id_rsa' -o -name 'id_ed25519' 2>/dev/null | head -1 | grep -q ."
- severity: critical

### no-tokens-in-source
- description: No hardcoded API tokens in the game file or docs
- run: "! grep -iE '(api[_-]?key|secret|token|password)\\s*[:=]\\s*[\"'\\''][A-Za-z0-9]{16,}' 688-attack-hub.html 2>/dev/null | head -1 | grep -q ."
- severity: critical

## Provenance

### author-correct
- description: Git author matches expected identity
- run: "git log -1 --format='%ae' | grep -qE '(hyperpolymath|j\\.d\\.a\\.jewell)'"
- severity: warning

### license-content
- description: LICENSE is the canonical AGPL-3.0-or-later text
- run: grep -q 'GNU AFFERO GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE' LICENSE
- severity: warning

## Sensitive areas requiring explicit approval

- GOVERNANCE.adoc
- MAINTAINERS.adoc
- .github/CODEOWNERS
- LICENSE / LICENSES/
- .machine_readable/descriptiles/CLADE.a2ml (repo identity — never copy another repo's UUID/name)
